Printer:

Get .deb package from
http://support.brother.com/g/b/downloadend.aspx?c=us&lang=en&prod=dcp7030_all&os=128&dlid=dlf005511_000&flang=4&type3=559
and it should be working. Alternatively search here:
http://welcome.solutions.brother.com/bsc/public_s/id/linux/en/download_prn.html

Scanner:

Get .deb package from
http://support.brother.com/g/b/downloadend.aspx?c=us&lang=en&prod=dcp7030_all&os=128&dlid=dlf006642_000&flang=4&type3=566
Alternatively search here:
http://welcome.solutions.brother.com/bsc/public_s/id/linux/en/download_prn.html
Install xsane.
If you get a "failed to open device" error in xsane, change the permissions. First find out where the Scanner resides with
lsusb
and then
chmod a+w /dev/bus/usb/$BUS/$DEVICE
You may have to redo the last step with setting the permission, every time you open xsane



